service.name: High Risk Medical Implantable Devices
service.description: The High Risk Medical Implantable Devices Register is a national patient contact register for implantable devices to ensure that patients with a high risk implantable device are contactable in the event of a serious safety risk associated with their device. This involved establishing nationally consistent data requirements, unique device identifiers and standard labelling for implantable devices, and a national protocol for rapid patient identification and notification.
